&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What the Role Is&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Babylist Media is transforming its operating model to support long-term, scalable growth. We are standing up a modern Revenue Operations organization focused on platform modernization, AI-enabled workflows, and scalable media operations. Reporting to the VP of Strategic Partnerships &amp;amp; Business Development, the Director of Revenue Operations will build and lead a high-performing team, guiding the strategy, systems, and cross-functional processes that drive our future revenue engine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience in advertising or media revenue operations, sales operations, with deep expertise in architecting scalable operating systems for growing media companies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant experience within media or advertising ecosystems, including working with publishers, advertisers, or ad-tech platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of proven leadership experience building and managing high-performing teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience managing advertising inventory and driving yield optimization strategies across onsite and offsite channels, leveraging pricing, packaging, forecasting, and performance analytics to maximize revenue and fill rates while balancing advertiser demand and user experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience building, launching, and managing ad-server programs, including implementation, optimization, and ongoing governance. Experience with Boostr or Koddi is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, financial, and operational acumen, with the ability to translate complex business needs into clear, scalable processes and systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of revenue funnels, forecasting, pipeline management, and sales processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading commission planning, territory design, and quota-setting processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills, with experience presenting recommendations and insights to executive leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A builder mentality—comfortable operating in ambiguity, creating structure, and scaling for future growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bias toward action, continuous improvement, and high-quality execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You naturally reach for AI in your work — at Babylist, every team uses AI daily. You&#39;re already using it to move faster and improve your output, and you stay curious about what&#39;s coming next&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Will Make An Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, performance manage and develop a growing team of three across Pricing &amp;amp; Packaging and Ad Operations for onsite and offsite channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee inventory management and yield optimization across all media products, maximizing sell-through rates while protecting margin&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee rate card strategy, pricing architecture, and new media product development to maximize yield and sell-through efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Ad Operations’ transition to a fully integrated Koddi ad server model (from site-served), owning trafficking, pacing, optimization, reconciliation, and serving as system owner for Koddi and Boostr (architecture, permissions, reporting integrity).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run the deal desk, reviewing pricing, discounting, and non-standard deals while supporting key account growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead annual planning and quarterly forecasting across GTM functions in partnership with Finance, building accurate pipeline and revenue models that inform both short- and long-term strategic decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Finance and Accounting on revenue actualization, monthly billing, and ensuring accurate revenue recognition processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee end-to-end commission operations (plan design,

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What the Role Is&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Babylist is looking for an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Branded Content Editor &lt;/strong&gt;who owns sponsored email from start to finish and leads how our team uses AI to build and scale that work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a writing and editing role first and foremost, one that requires equal parts creativity and love of process (we know you&#39;re out there!). You&#39;re writing and designing on one hand, managing deadlines and multiple projects on the other. And if you had a third hand, it&#39;d be dedicated to Slack. It&#39;s where we connect, solve problems, share wins, and send all the emojis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gets a genuine kick out of finding exactly the right words.&lt;/strong&gt; Clever subject lines, unexpected word combos, copy that earns the click.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exceptional writer and editor with a sharp brand voice.&lt;/strong&gt; Writes fast and accurately, and can adapt a message to meet client and user needs without losing Babylist&#39;s tone.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fluent in AI tools&lt;/strong&gt; (Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini, etc.) for research, outlining, data collection, automations, and more to improve the team&#39;s production workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proficient in Figma,&lt;/strong&gt; comfortable building and QA&#39;ing email.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data-driven,&lt;/strong&gt; reads performance data and knows how to act on it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systems-oriented,&lt;/strong&gt; spots bottlenecks and builds solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Natural relationship builder,&lt;/strong&gt; treats cross-functional partnerships as essential to getting the best work done.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clear communicator,&lt;/strong&gt; knows when to flag an issue, when to push back, and when to let it go.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Handles client and legal revisions efficiently&lt;/strong&gt; and protects the user experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4+ years&lt;/strong&gt; writing and editing branded content, or at a digital publisher or media company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You naturally reach for AI in your work. At Babylist, every team uses AI daily. You&#39;re already using it to move faster and improve your output, and you stay curious about what&#39;s coming next.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Will Make An Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write, edit, build in Figma, and QA branded email before it ships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set and document the standards for branded email: voice, quality, and production process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop AI-assisted workflows that reduce manual production time across the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach the team on how to use AI tools you discover and develop so everyone levels up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pull and analyze email performance data; use what you learn to adjust copy and hit benchmarks. Report monthly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage multiple assignments simultaneously and hit deadlines in a high-volume environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flex into other branded content as priorities shift: articles, newsletter placements, feed copy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We use a market-based approach to compensation. The starting salary range for this role is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;$119,852 to $143,839&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your starting salary will be based on your location, experience, and qualifications, with increases over time tied to performance, role growth, and internal pay equity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bab

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Babylist, the work our fulfillment teams do reaches millions of families across the country — whether you&#39;re on the floor moving product or leading the operation that makes it happen. We&#39;re one of the leading platforms for expecting and new families — a $750M business with 10 million customers and eight consecutive years of profitability. Our fulfillment centers are where the mission becomes real, and the people who run them are a core part of how we deliver on it every single day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Ways of Working&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our fulfillment teams work on-site in a fast-paced, team-driven environment where every role — from the floor to leadership — plays a direct part in delivering the Babylist experience to millions of families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What the Role Is&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Babylist, we help families prepare for one of the biggest moments of their lives — and our Commercial Point Fulfillment Center is where that promise becomes real. As a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Forklift Operator,&lt;/strong&gt; you&#39;re a core part of making that happen. You&#39;ll move product accurately and safely across our distribution center, working alongside a team that genuinely looks out for each other. This is a role where skilled, dependable people are valued — and rewarded for it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The schedule for this role is Monday- Thursday 7:30pm- 6:00am at our Fulfillment Center located in Commercial Point, OH.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Certified and experienced on multiple lift types&lt;/strong&gt; — you&#39;re comfortable on a Reach Truck, Cherry Picker, Stand-Up Forklift, and Sit-Down Forklift (3+ years on each)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Safety is non-negotiable for you&lt;/strong&gt; — you follow protocols because you understand why they exist, not because someone&#39;s watching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Steady and dependable&lt;/strong&gt; — your team counts on you to show up, stay on task, and keep things moving even when volume spikes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adaptable across zones and tasks&lt;/strong&gt; — shifting priorities don&#39;t throw you; you read the floor and adjust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A real teammate&lt;/strong&gt; — you communicate clearly, flag issues early, and help others hit the shared goal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Will Make an Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Move, locate, stack, and count materials throughout the distribution center using the full range of lift equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Load and unload trailers safely — keeping outbound on schedule and inbound organized&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support both inbound and outbound operations with accurate, timely material handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform pre-shift equipment inspections and flag maintenance needs before they become problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep your work area clean, organized, and hazard-free — every shift, not just when audited&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Step in to support other warehouse functions when the floor needs it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why This Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;ll know exactly when your next raise is coming&lt;/strong&gt; — structured pay increases every 3 months through your first 18 months, no guessing, no waiting to be noticed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The schedule is consistent and predictable&lt;/strong&gt; — you can plan your life around this job, not the other way around&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The team here is the real deal&lt;/strong&gt; — people who take their work seriously, back each other up, and make a long shift feel a lot shorter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;T

