&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What the Role Is&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Babylist’s finance and accounting operations run on NetSuite, and as the business scales, so does the complexity of keeping that platform aligned with the real needs of our accounting, finance, and operations teams. As our Senior NetSuite Functional Analyst, you will be the deep functional expert on NetSuite’s financial modules — partnering directly with accounting and finance to translate business needs into practical solutions, and working alongside our existing NetSuite Developer and NetSuite Administrator to ensure the platform enables rather than hinders day-to-day operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join a small, tight-knit NetSuite pod inside our Financial Systems team. This pod owns the full lifecycle of NetSuite work: you lead the functional “what and why” (and often the “how” that stays within native NetSuite), the Developer owns custom SuiteScript development, and the Administrator owns system administration and day-to-day operational support. You will report to our Staff Technical Product Manager for Financial Operations and partner closely with Engineering, Accounting, Finance, and Operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience implementing or operating ERP solutions and financial operations processes, with deep hands-on NetSuite experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A NetSuite functional subject matter expert across the financial modules: GL, AP, AR, Revenue Recognition, Fixed Assets, ARM, SuiteBilling, and Consolidations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Defaults NetSuite’s native capabilities are cold and default to them before proposing custom development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has partnered directly with accounting and finance teams through close, audit, and operational cycles — you speak their language and understand their day-to-day pain points.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brings a working command of the technical toolkit — SuiteScript, workflows, SuiteApps, NetSuite APIs, saved searches, and dashboards — enough to design sound solutions and collaborate with developers even if you are not writing production scripts yourself.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced working with NetSuite as part of a broader financial operations ecosystem that includes custom-built applications, P2P systems, and ancillary tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills; you can move between an accountant, an engineer, and a VP in the same meeting without losing anyone.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with ambiguity and can translate vague business pain into clear, actionable functional requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated capabilities working in an AI first development environment leveraging tools like Claude Code, Devin amongst others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus: prior experience in a high-growth ecommerce, consumer, or marketplace environment; prior experience as a NetSuite Administrator.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;re genuinely excited about what AI can do -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;not just as a concept, but as something you want to get your hands on. At Babylist, every team uses AI daily, and we&#39;re looking for people who lean in.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Will Make An Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the deep subject matter expert on NetSuite’s financial modules, advising Accounting, Finance, and Engineering on best practices and optimal configuration before custom development is pursued.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary systems partner for our accounting and finance teams — translating business needs into functional solutions within NetSuite, supporting close processes, and ensuring NetSuite enables rather than hinders day-to-day operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the “what and why” (and in many cases the “how”) for intra-NetSuite work: business requirements, solution design

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What the Role Is&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The modern tech stack has collapsed the distance between designing an experience and shipping it. We&#39;re hiring Senior Product Designers to build the next generation of Babylist by leveraging this reality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; Senior Product Designer&lt;/strong&gt; is the primary owner for user experience, delight, and interaction quality on the team. Equal parts skilled designer, hands-on researcher, and AI-enabled builder, you own how things feel, think broadly about user flows across the full Babylist experience, and hold the bar for whether something is intuitive, beautiful, and emotionally right for the user. You work alongside product managers, engineers, and data partners, but you are the one driving the experience layer and making sure every interaction meets both the functional and emotional needs of our users to drive impactful outcomes for the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You flex beyond the basics by running research, standing up working prototypes (in hours not days), and contributing to production-quality front-end code ensuring polish is never a trade-off. You help Babylist make the transition into AI-native product development by modeling what an AI-native designer does every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you shape how parents discover products, receive gifts, and navigate early parenthood across web and native mobile. These are not casual interactions. Families are making decisions during one of the most meaningful and overwhelming transitions of their lives. The experience has to be easy to use, easy to understand, and worthy of the trust they place in us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Craft and experience obsessed&lt;/strong&gt;. You care deeply about how things feel, not just how they function. You notice the details most people can&#39;t articulate but everyone responds to like transitions, motion, and accessibility. You hold the high bar for delight and have a portfolio of shipped consumer product work across web and native mobile that demonstrates this.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A systems thinker.&lt;/strong&gt; You see the full picture. You think about how a single interaction fits into a broader flow, how flows connect across products, and how the design system enables all of it. You design for coherence, not just screens.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Industry aware and pattern fluent.&lt;/strong&gt; You stay current with modern product design, not to follow trends but to borrow what&#39;s proven and challenge what&#39;s stale. You know the interaction patterns, design system conventions, and digital product best practices that have become table stakes, and you know when to apply them or evolve them when Babylist families need something different.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Human-and-data-centered.&lt;/strong&gt; You know how to leverage (and plan and run) generative and evaluative research to unlock actionable insights that guide product decisions. You bring concrete qualitative and quantitative evidence into design decisions and share clear, persuasive design rationale via concise and impactful communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product savvy&lt;/strong&gt;. You know what&#39;s worth building and what isn&#39;t, what UX is right for a given context, and what will actually resonate with users in ways that support the business’ top line goals. You make engineers and product managers faster, not slower, by reducing ambiguity and tightening the scope of what needs to be solved.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Critical thinker.&lt;/strong&gt; You question assumptions and stress-test ideas before committing to them, distinguishing between what the data says and what people want it to say. You approach problems with creativity and multi-dimensional thinking.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li

